"The role and impact of social media in modern society"

Social media has become an integral part of everyday life for people around the world, changing the way people communicate, information flow and interact in society. In this paper, we will examine the role of social media and its impact on modern society and discuss the positive and negative aspects of its use.

1. Communication and social networking
Social media provide an opportunity to connect and communicate with people around the world. They make it easy to share information, find old friends, make new acquaintances, and keep in touch across distances.

2. Influence on public opinion
Social media have become an important factor in shaping public opinion. They provide a platform for expressing opinions, disseminating information and mobilising the public on various issues.

3. Impact on mental health
The use of social media can have both positive and negative effects on mental health. On the one hand, they help spread positive information and support communities. On the other hand, they can lead to excessive comparative judgement, negative impacts of social standards and inflated stress levels.
